TABLE 6 

Comparison of different feature aggregation strategies on seven datasets. 1: Only aggregating the low-level features (Conv1∼3), 
2: Only aggregating the high-level features (Conv3∼5), 3: Directly integrating all five-level features (Conv1∼5) by a single 
decoder, 4: Our model without the refinement flow, 5: High-level features (Conv3∼5) are first refined by the initial map aggregated 
by low-level features (Conv1∼3) and are then integrated to generate the final saliency map, and 6: The proposed cascaded 
refinement mechanism.
